long_desc.thetext:
There was a question asked at "Stack Overflow": http://stackoverflow.com/questions/19399466/qooxdoo-custom-listitem-with-button
I stripped the code down to provide a better playground sample as starting point (probably it can be stripped down even more): http://tinyurl.com/mesqsth
Note: This uses 3.0.1 playground but issue also applies for devel.
Reproduce: 1) click topmost button 2) scroll via scroll bar (not mouse wheel!) 3) click other button
Result: Another button gets focus and triggers action Should: Clicked button should get focus and trigger action
The unwanted behavior doesn't occur if:
* Modern theme is used: qx.theme.manager.Meta.getInstance().setTheme(qx.theme.Modern);
* Or no padding is given: list.setPadding(0);
* Or Focus is disabled: list.setFocusable(false);
